=#628CBC>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=#004088 class=headings><font color=#628CBC>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughtersofmalaeliu>DaughtersOfMalaeliu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Penny Priddy</span><br>  Posts: 177<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/9/03 10:37:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=1>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~chasingsusan/women.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Loss of Faith- part II</span><hr size=1> Malaehi’s face was white with shock and bewilderment as she watched the Paladin walk away.  She had spent the past few weeks trying to make sense of her dreams and the voice she heard.  Of all people, she had found a clue with a fallen Paladin.  He spoke of a realm that matched her dream precisely.  <br>
<br>
The home of Bristlebane.<br>
<br>
Malaehi ventured to the Temple of Veeshan and waited patiently to join a war party to travel safely through the lair of the fierce Dragons and enter the Plane of Mischief.<br>
<br>
She spent the next week wandering the walls of the Castle until she finally found what she was looking for.  The ballroom matched the scene from Malaehi’s dream perfectly.  It all made perfect sense now.<br>
<br>
She found Erollisi Marr and threw herself down at the feet of the Goddess and wept.  But, the Goddess stared across the room with glass eyes and an empty smile, dancing around, mindlessly.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~chasingsusan/EMarr.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
The voice whispered in her ear… <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Yes, it is true.  You have put your faith in a puppet.  You have fought for no one but yourself and those around you, enchantress.”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi whirled around quickly and at last saw the one who’s voice had haunted her.  He was a human, but wraithlike in appearance, wearing the garments of a prisoner.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Who are you!?”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The gaunt man chuckled and leaned upon a staff wearily, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“I am called many things… The Forsaken… the UnGod … the Mad… but, what is a name?”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> he shrugged and hobbled through the crimson fog, disappearing.<br>
<br>
Malaehi turned back to her Goddess and gently gathered the doll into her arms and hugged her to her chest.  Murmuring words of forgiveness she stepped into a blue-grey portal and left Bristlebane’s abode.<br>
 <p>Malaehi d'Aeliu - Phantasmist, in the service of Erollisi Marr<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~chasingsusan"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~chasingsusan/BEAUTY.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughtersofmalaeliu>DaughtersOfMalaeliu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Penny Priddy</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/9/03 12:00:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~chasingsusan/women.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Loss of Faith- part III</span><hr size=1> One by one they fell and it all began to make much sense to the Enchantress.  She recalled being awestruck by the Gods and their power.  Evil Innoruuk had sent his minions to slaughter all those invading his realm.  When the time was right, and the army was strong enough, she would see him die again and again.  <br>
<br>
Riding her mount, Kingwell, through Lesser Faydark, she recalled laying eyes on the fearful Cazic Thule when he faced off with the tree-hugging sprite Tunare.  The result was a ruined land.  Later she would see Cazic Thule in his own realm and eventually trod across his fallen body.  He was no more than a mighty, powerful beast; nothing to be deified.<br>
<br>
But, what of the rest?  Terris Thule, Saryrn, the Zek twins and Bertoxxulous, … all so called Gods, but lay dead like cattle.<br>
<br>
Praise be to the Gods of the light…<br>
<br>
Malaehi paused and shifted in her saddle.  Kingwell nickered softly, warning the enchantress of an intruder.  The frail man emerged from the Faydark fog and caressed Kingwell’s soft nose.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Where were those Gods of the light when this land was cursed?  Why would they not instantly come to your aid when you called?  Why did they allow so many to suffer and perish in battle….”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> His voice grew louder into a shout, echoing through the forest… <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Only to allow you to be resurrected and die again?!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
He turned to the forest and raised his staff  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Where are you when we need you?  Why do you toy with us?!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
He paused and crouched low to the ground and listened, like a crazed person… <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Shh... You hear that?”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi listened intently, straining to hear.  <br>
<br>
Suddenly the man was upon Kingwell’s back and behind Malaehi in the saddle, holding her tight with his staff across her throat, choking her.  Kingwell took off into a terrified run through the forest at breakneck speed.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Call for Erollisi NOW!!!  Do IT!!  Where is she?”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi closed her eyes and focused her magic on escaping in anyway, but the man was relentless with his grip, laughing in her ear the whole time.  She prayed to her Goddess, but remembered that her Goddess was a doll, stuffed away in her backpack tied to Kingwell’s saddle.  She had to do something fast, she could not breathe.  She sent her thoughts out into a pure clear stream of thought. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>&quot;Help me, my love&quot;</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Call to her… CALL to any of them… they ARE DEAD!!!  Or they just do not CARE!  Do you hear me?!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Tears and the sharp cold wind stung Mala’s cheeks as she felt Kingwell take flight into the air.  The sharp smell of sulfur struck the air as a thunderbolt bounced harmlessly off the back of the madman.  Below on the ground, stood Xendapus chanting and firing off explosions aimed at the madman.<br>
<br>
Then the world went black and tilted left.<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
Malaehi woke up in Xendapus’ room, again with his worried face near hers.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“There, there she is!  Bah, elf!  You will be the death of me!” </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The gnome sighed.  Mala struggled to speak, but the Gnome put a finger over her lips saying:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“I found something you may want to snuggle with!” </strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> He cackled and hopped off the bed and returned with the Erollisi Marr puppet in his hands.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Look!  A Dolly!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> he rambled on missing the look of shock and terror in the enchantress’ eyes <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“… just tuck her under your chin and snuggle up for a while.  I need to run out and let everyone know you are fine… hush hush just sleep!”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi waited for Xend to leave, before crawling out of bed, grabbing her things and gating back to Plane of Tranquility.  She entered her home on the hill and walked around to her meditation garden.  She settled in and slipped into a trance and deep thought.<br>
<br>
Hours later, she got up refreshed and determined.  She summoned Kingwell and put the doll into his saddleback and sent him off to graze.  Her courier came in with a message.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Milady, evil has invade the land of Tunare and the Council of Faydark and the ancients of Erollisi Marr seek your aid in stopping them.”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi spat in disgust, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“after the abuse the Ancients of Erollisi put me through … torturing me because I fell in love… because I gave myself to a male.  NOW, they want my help…”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Malaehi recalled the searing pain of being flogged and starved for her “crime”, for breaking her vow of chastity; they would have taken her life, had it not been for the intervention of Kae, the mysterious enchantress who was a member of the Council.<br>
<br>
She had left the sect of the Goddess and continued to worship her on her own.  But, to what avail…<br>
 <p>Malaehi d'Aeliu - Phantasmist, in the service of Erollisi Marr<br>
<!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://home.attbi.com/~chasingsusan"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://home.attbi.com/~chasingsusan/BEAUTY.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughtersofmalaeliu>DaughtersOfMalaeliu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_lightning.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Penny Priddy</span><br>  Posts: 179<br> <font color=#628CBC>(1/9/03 1:00:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm11.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=26.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://home.attbi.com/~chasingsusan/women.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Loss of Faith- part IV</span><hr size=1> Darkness covered the sky as Malaehi stepped into the Realm of Tunare.  The land was bare and quiet.  She called out into the emptiness:  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>“Please I beg of you, for the love of all that is holy and sacred, leave this land now, untouched and unspoiled!  This is the realm of the Mother of All.  Leave her in peace.”</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Her call was returned with familiar voices… Krastus, the evil Knight who has hunted by her side for ages, aye hating her to the core, but protecting her more often than not.  Then the chillingly evil voice of the dead himself, Patron of the House Rea’Morda, beckoning the enchantress in a mocking manner, to join in on the hunt.  <br>
<br>
As she rode Kingwell through the battle scarred land, she recalled the times where the evil one himself had summoned her corpse from the dead, aiding her in battle many times.<br>
<br>
One by one familiar voices, Cortusa, Kogbender, Maedaria, Charaniki, and more.  Voices whom she was told she should hate because of the God they follow.  But, she never hated them.  No, the love of the Goddess impelled Malaehi to convince these lost souls to stop their evil ways and return to the light from where they were snatched ever so long ago by their evil Gods.  Now, she was ordered to slay these for invading Tunare’s realm?!  <br>
<br>
She rode closer to the war party.<br>
<br>
The coldest voice cut through the land, the one whom she feared the most:  Rusalka, Matron of the House, High Priestess of Innoruuk.  The same one who brought Malaehi back from the dead countless times, who stood side by side as they brought Innoruuk to his knees.<br>
<br>
She paused in thought as she rounded the bend and looked down at the hunters. She frowned and decided to disobey the orders of the Faydark Champions, ripping the missive to shreds.  She would not attempt to slaughter these people, nor die trying.<br>
<br>
Approaching the party she expected to be killed as swiftly as they killed the pumas.  But, she was greeted and invited to join in.  Mala tried again to dissuade them from hunting in these holy lands… but even those words sounded dead on her tongue.<br>
<br>
What made these lands holy and Innoruuk’s defiled?<br>
<br>
The voice of laughter resounded in her ears, the voice of the madman, the voice of the Forsaken.  He was Zebuxoruk. And he was right.<br>
<br>
Malaehi joined in the battle and fought furiously, just as she had done in the other realms of the Gods.<br>
~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~<br>
<br>
The next day, she was with another army in the Halls of Honor, where she stood on top of the corpse of Mithaniel Marr, twin of her Goddess and a worthy foe.<br>
<br>
Malaehi threw her head back and roared in victory!<br>
<br>
Faith in the Gods was dead to her; however, faith in those she hunted with took its place in her heart.  She was scared, no doubt, but free. <p>Malaehi d'Aeliu - Phantasmist, in the service of Erollisi Marr<br>
